                  </hi>. I am a clerk, and live on the premises of Messrs. Leaf, in Wood-street, Cheapside. On the 29th of Aug., about three o'clock in the afternoon, I was in Cateaton-street—I felt something at my coat pocket—I turned round, and saw the prisoner running away with a handkerchief in his hand, which was mine, and had been in my pocket just before—I pur<lb></lb>sued, and saw him throw it down—I took it up—it is my property.</p>
